										<footer class="article-contributor contributors">
									

<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Tess Gallagher</span></strong> is a poet, fiction writer, essayist, screenwriter, and translator. Her latest poetry collection is titled <em>Dear Ghosts,</em> (Graywolf Press). Her forthcoming book <em>Distant Rain</em> (Eastern Washington Press) is a conversation with Buddhist nun Jakucho Setouchi. She lives in Port Angeles, Washington.</p><a href="/contributors/tess-gallagher" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

